description.narrative: Oxfam Novib will be responsible for facilitating the learning exchange programme E-Motive. Other stakeholders involved include AVSI(in Uganda and South Sudan) and Oxfam (in South Sudan), and ministry officials, school leadership and School management committees,Parents teachers association, learners and community as learners and implementers of the best practice (identified elsewhere) adapted to their own context. Oxfam Novib will also build capacity of local partners in Uganda (notably Oxfam, AVSI and FAWE) and South Sudan (Oxfam, AVSI and CDI) to facilitate human-centered design of (improvement of) infrastructure of and around schools, by organizing an Online training (with possibilities to include off-line elements) on methodologies to work with stakeholders (learners, teachers, community members, education officials, out-of-school children, architects) on identifying the needs and designing adequate and cost-effective school infrastructure. The training includes research on local context and with local stakeholders, and prototyping the design.

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib was founded in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Oxfam Novib is member of the Oxfam International confederation. Working together in the confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib's main office is based in The Netherlands, it supports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fundraising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s the Hague office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
